Kowloon reads Akh'enet's Reed Ledger Warden tradition — water first, records second, ritual never above either — as a founding-philosophy alignment with its own Neon Covenant doctrine: practical civic infrastructure is what institutional legitimacy serves, not exploits. The divergence that destroyed Akh'enet (Jackal Balance Court fusing debt adjudication with funerary sentence rites until institutional vocabularies became indistinguishable) parallels Kowloon's resistance to Ash Cult theological framing of volcanic events as divine judgment. Cistern infrastructure producing broken pressure logic, irregular echoes, and bioluminescent mineral films is an engineering phenomenon; Sepulchrist reinterpretation as spiritual judgment is the same category confusion Kowloon's civic design prevents. The Neon Covenant's "one ledger, one ration code" principle and the Wardens' civic doctrine share structure: documentation precision as survival instrument, not metaphysical authority. Akh'enet's Bellwind Collapse — hydraulic failure that was interpreted as theological — demonstrates what happens when engineering resources are depleted and theological interpretation captures the vacuum.

