Akh'enet's most significant catastrophe in Khenari terms is the mass ledger loss in the Bellwind Collapse: archive vaults flooded and silted, destroying records through which civic and funerary descent chains could be traced. Persons who passed through Akh'enet's administrative systems and whose passage was documented now have those documents destroyed — a mass production of spiritual gaps. The Jackal Balance Court's sentence-binding practices represent a different Khenari concern: records created as instruments of coercion rather than spiritual continuity. A sentence-binding on a living debtor is not sacred record-keeping; it is sacred record-vocabulary used to accomplish civil punishment. Khenari practitioners distinguish the Reed Ledger Wardens' approach (records as civic survival) from the Jackal Balance Court's approach (records as authority vehicles) as the distinction between honest and dishonest documentation. The Nadir Palace engine — the Sepulchrists' goal of restored "final lawful resonance" — would, in Khenari terms, convert an entire city into a vehicle for authority-claims in descent vocabulary, closing pathways rather than maintaining them.

